  "prompt": "Which are the least expensive and still good 3D/4D cinema theaters in Delhi NCR?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, I can provide general recommendations based on popular theaters known for offering a good balance between price and quality. However, specific ticket prices can vary based on the movie, time, and any ongoing promotions. Here are a few theaters you might consider:\n\n1. **PVR Cinemas**: While some locations can be a bit pricey, PVR often has budget-friendly shows, especially during weekdays and matinee screenings. Look for PVR theaters in places like DLF Mall of Noida and PVR Saket.\n\n2. **Cinepolis**: Known for its comfortable seating and good viewing experience, Cinepolis often has competitive pricing, especially for early screenings and certain days of the week.\n\n3. **INOX**: Similar to PVR, INOX has some locations that offer reasonable rates, especially during off-peak hours. The INOX in Sector 18, Noida, is popular and sometimes has special offers.\n\n4. **Movie Time**: Located in some parts of Delhi NCR, Movie Time offers a good cinematic experience at relatively lower prices compared to bigger chains.\n\n5. **Raj Cinema**: This is a more budget-friendly option that screens both mainstream and regional films. It may not have the latest in 3D/4D technology, but it can be a cost-effective option.\n\n6. **Wave Cinemas**: They often provide a good movie experience at a reasonable price and have locations in areas like Noida and Delhi.\n\n7. **SRS Cinemas**: Found in various locations, SRS offers competitive pricing with multiple screens, including 3D.\n\nIt\u2019s always a good idea to check for online ticket booking platforms for discounts and offers. Additionally, keep an eye on local promotions or loyalty programs that can provide lower prices for regular moviegoers.",
